  "prompt": "Will Stephen Hawking win a Nobel Prize?",
  "response": "Stephen Hawking, the renowned theoretical physicist, passed away in March 2018. While he made significant contributions to the fields of cosmology and quantum gravity, particularly in relation to black holes and the nature of the universe, the Nobel Prize is typically awarded for discoveries that can be experimentally validated. Many of Hawking's theories, such as Hawking radiation, remain unproven due to the challenges associated with measuring such phenomena. \n\nAs of now, since he has passed away, he will not be awarded a Nobel Prize. The Nobel Prizes are generally not awarded posthumously, except in rare cases where a nominee dies after the announcement but before the award ceremony.",
